<title>GERMANY: MAN Roland plans further job losses.</title>
<headline>MAN Roland plans further job losses.</headline>
<dateline>OFFENBACH, Germany 1997-03-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>German printing group MAN Roland AG, a unit of engineering group MAN AG, said on Thursday that lower-than-expected sales growth meant further job would be needed this year.</p>
<p>The group said it would cut 400 jobs in the Rhine-Main region and the group forecasts a payroll of 3,950 employees by the end of 1997.</p>
<p>MAN Roland said in a statement that the expected pick-up in demand for offset printing machinery had not come about and in the mid-term the group expected no increase in sales.</p>
<p>This would necessitate further costs and an increase in capacity, the group said.</p>
<p>MAN Roland said the job cuts would come through natural wastage. In the year to the end of June 1996, the group reported a pre-tax loss of 83 million marks, compared to a loss of 146 million marks the previous year.</p>
